<%= content_for(:navbar_class, "navbar-guide") %>

<a href="" class="top-link hide" id="scrollToTop"><i class="fas fa-3x fa-chevron-circle-up"></i></a>
<div class="banner-guide">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Univerlay Step-by-Step Guide</h1>
    <h6>How to use the Univerlay Chrome Extension for painless digital adoption!</h6>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <br>
  <div id="steps-guide" class="p-5">
    <h3><b>Overview</b></h3>
    <p>Univerlay is a Digital Adoption Platform (DAP) that provides training information and step-by-step guides within the web browser, to make the digital adoption journey painless.</p>
    <p>This step-by-step guide will bring you through the whole onboarding process to Univerlay.</p>
    <h3><b>Starting a lesson with Univerlay</b></h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0;"><em>*Skip to Step 3 if you've already signed up for an Univerlay account and has downloaded the Univerlay Chrome Extension.</em></p>
    <p><em>*Skip to Step 2 if you've already signed up for an Univerlay account but yet to downloaded the Univerlay Chrome Extension.</em></p>

    <h5><b>Step 1:</b></h5>
    <p>Sign up for an account <%= link_to "here", new_user_registration_path %>.</p>
    <%= image_tag ("sign-up.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>

    <h5><b>Step 2:</b></h5>
    <p>Download Univerlay Chrome Extension from the <a href="" target="_blank">Chrome Web Store</a>.</p>

    <h5><b>Step 3:</b></h5>
    <p>Choose a lesson to start from our list of <a href="https://www.univerlay.me/#lessons-section" target="_blank">lessons</a>.</p>
    <%= image_tag ("start-lesson.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>
    <br>

    <h5><b>Step 4:</b></h5>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0;">Click on the 'Click to lesson' button and it will direct you to the website (e.g. Github).</p>
    <p><em>*For Github lessons, remember to sign in or create an account with Github.</em></p>
    <%= image_tag ("click-to-lesson.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>
    <br>

    <h5><b>Step 5:</b></h5>
    <p>Once signed in to the current website (e.g. Github), start the Univerlay Chrome Extension and enter your Univerlay account email and password. Then, click 'Submit' button below the 'password' field.</p>
    <%= image_tag ("start-extension.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>

    <h5><b>Step 6:</b></h5>
    <p>Choose your lesson from the dropdown menu, and click the 'Submit' button below the dropdown menu. Voila! You should have a popup appearing on the page, and you can proceed to start your learning with Univerlay :)</p>
    <%= image_tag ("choose-lesson.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>

    <h5><b>Step 7:</b></h5>
    <p>Click on 'Clear' button on Univerlay Chrome Extension popup to sign out of your session.</p>
    <%= image_tag ("clear-session.gif"), height: 300, class: "mb-4" %>
  </div>
  <br>
</div>
